******
[2]
Date: Fri 6 Aug 2021 1:19 PM
Source: RIA (Republican Information Agency) Dagestan [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
https://riadagestan.ru/news/karabudakhkentskiy_rayon/v_karabudakhkentskom_rayone_prinimayutsya_mery_po_profilaktike_sibirskoy_yazvy/


The meeting of the sanitary-anti-epidemic commission was chaired by the head of the district, Mahmud Amiraliyev. The event took place yesterday [Thu 5 Aug 2021] in the building of the administration of the village of Kakashura, the press service of the municipality told the news agency.

The meeting was also attended by the head of the service for supervision in the field of consumer rights protection and human well-being of the Republic of Dagestan, Nikolay Pavlov; the deputy head of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia for the Karabudakhkent region for the UUP, Ruslan Khalduzov; the chief doctor of the Central Regional Hospital, Rasul Giravov; the head of the Department of Rospotrebnadzor RD for the city of Kaspiysk and the Karabudakhkent region Abacharaev; and the heads of the veterinary department and the Department of Agriculture of the Republic of Moldova.

The meeting participants discussed the issues of taking measures to prevent anthrax. On [31 Jul 2021], a resident of the village of Kakashura went to the surgical department of the Caspian city's Hospital with a complaint about an unhealed wound. He was admitted to hospital with a preliminary diagnosis of anthrax. Currently, the patient is admitted to the infectious diseases department of the Gurbukinsky district hospital. According to the press service "the infection was caused by cutting the carcass of an infected bull".

