[Our thanks to Mahmoud, yet again, for this report.

Dagestan is an autonomous republic of Russia. It is small -- 19 400 square miles and 2.9 million people -- on the north west Caspian Sea coast and adjoins Azerbaijan, Chechnya, and Georgia. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dagestan.

Latterly, OIE has reported limited outbreaks in 2005, 2010, and 2012, but nothing since. Because of the civil unrest in the country, we may presume that the disease is underreported, though sporadic. This apparently singular case resulted yet again from the careless butchering of a bull that had died of anthrax. I would not be surprised if there had not been other livestock dead from anthrax in this village at the same time. - Mod.MHJ

